HEADWORD: Piepowder
<hw>Pie"pow`der</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Lit., dustyfoot, i. e., dusty-footed dealers, fr. F.
<ets>pied</ets> foot + <ets>poudreux</ets> dusty.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng.
Law)</fld> <def>An ancient court of record in England, formerly incident
to every fair and market, of which the steward of him who owned or had
the toll was the judge.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

